.  aThe concept of alienation has returned. In this volume, it is theorized at the interface of sociology, social philosophy and social psychology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Okt 2018) 4a2000er-Jahre. 4aAlfred Lorenzer. 4aAneignung. 4aAppropriation Strategies. 4aCritical Theory. 4aHistory of Philosophy. 4aIdentity. 4aIdentität. 4aKarl Marx. 4aKritische Theorie. 4aPhilosophiegeschichte. 4aPierre Bourdieu. 4aPsychoanalyse. 4aPsychoanalysis. 4aSocial Relations. 4aSociological Theory. 4aSociology. 4aSozialität. 4aSoziologie. 4aSoziologische Theorie. 4aSubject. 4aSubjekt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2018z9783110603231oZDB-23-DSW40uhttps://doi.org/10.14361/9783839445525zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783839445525.jpg  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA14ALL  aPDA15STM  aPDA16SSH  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA3STM  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DSWb2018